00:27:13.020 --> 00:27:13.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:27:13.550 --> 00:27:13.790 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Right?

00:27:13.790 --> 00:27:14.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Connection.

00:27:14.500 --> 00:27:15.250 align:middle line:90%
That's a good one.

00:27:15.250 --> 00:27:18.360 align:middle line:84%
Because the heart is connected
electrically and our whole body

00:27:18.360 --> 00:27:19.375 align:middle line:90%
is connected.

00:27:19.375 --> 00:27:20.750 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, when that
breaks, but we're

00:27:20.750 --> 00:27:23.540 align:middle line:84%
not-- so speaking
of connection, we

00:27:23.540 --> 00:27:26.340 align:middle line:84%
have such a ridiculously
busy, fast paced world,

00:27:26.340 --> 00:27:28.960 align:middle line:84%
and we've gotten really
addicted to the phones.

00:27:28.960 --> 00:27:31.784 align:middle line:84%
And where you could be sitting
for five seconds waiting

00:27:31.784 --> 00:27:33.950 align:middle line:84%
for someone to come back
and you're just immediately

00:27:33.950 --> 00:27:37.870 align:middle line:84%
on the-- you know, there's that
real propensity to disconnect

00:27:37.870 --> 00:27:40.940 align:middle line:84%
all the time with the
smartphones or whatever it is.

00:27:40.940 --> 00:27:47.450 align:middle line:84%
So what do you see in the body
that has sacrificed internally

00:27:47.450 --> 00:27:49.890 align:middle line:84%
from that disconnection
with people?

00:27:49.890 --> 00:27:51.990 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: So that's
a great question.

00:27:51.990 --> 00:27:54.270 align:middle line:84%
You know, when you
said that we disconnect

00:27:54.270 --> 00:27:56.420 align:middle line:84%
when we are on our phone,
what's interesting is

00:27:56.420 --> 00:28:00.560 align:middle line:84%
I think people believe that this
is actually them connecting.

00:28:00.560 --> 00:28:01.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's true.

00:28:01.540 --> 00:28:04.732 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: And they are
getting stimulation by this.

00:28:04.732 --> 00:28:05.690 align:middle line:90%
Is there another tweet?

00:28:05.690 --> 00:28:06.970 align:middle line:84%
Is there another--
like, what's next?

00:28:06.970 --> 00:28:07.395 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:28:07.395 --> 00:28:08.103 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Right?

00:28:08.103 --> 00:28:10.650 align:middle line:90%
What's the latest this?

00:28:10.650 --> 00:28:12.860 align:middle line:84%
And so what I think
has happened is

00:28:12.860 --> 00:28:16.566 align:middle line:84%
we seem to think that our
head and what we're thinking

00:28:16.566 --> 00:28:18.440 align:middle line:84%
and what we're getting
from the outside world

00:28:18.440 --> 00:28:20.470 align:middle line:90%
is where we get our information.

00:28:20.470 --> 00:28:24.080 align:middle line:84%
And even though it's only an
18 inch drop to your heart,

00:28:24.080 --> 00:28:27.750 align:middle line:84%
I actually believe this is
where we get our information.

00:28:27.750 --> 00:28:32.120 align:middle line:84%
And so I think there's a way in
our busy, over stimulated world

00:28:32.120 --> 00:28:34.360 align:middle line:84%
that we have begun
to function just

00:28:34.360 --> 00:28:37.020 align:middle line:84%
from our head and
our thoughts, and we

00:28:37.020 --> 00:28:39.810 align:middle line:84%
get most of that input
from the outside world.

00:28:39.810 --> 00:28:41.570 align:middle line:84%
And so I think what
we've sacrificed

00:28:41.570 --> 00:28:46.150 align:middle line:84%
is actually turning up the
volume of our own hearts

00:28:46.150 --> 00:28:49.730 align:middle line:84%
and what we want and
listening to ourselves.

00:28:49.730 --> 00:28:52.120 align:middle line:84%
Instead, we have a
much greater focus

00:28:52.120 --> 00:28:55.802 align:middle line:84%
on external and other people's
ideas of what is correct.

00:28:55.802 --> 00:28:57.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Wow, this is
such key information

00:28:57.510 --> 00:29:00.580 align:middle line:84%
because one of the things
that I've always remembered

00:29:00.580 --> 00:29:06.670 align:middle line:84%
is a person who did hospice care
and spent thousands of hours

00:29:06.670 --> 00:29:08.870 align:middle line:84%
at the bedside of
people who passed over.

00:29:08.870 --> 00:29:09.820 align:middle line:90%
Or not passed over.

00:29:09.820 --> 00:29:11.940 align:middle line:90%
That are about to pass over.

00:29:11.940 --> 00:29:14.470 align:middle line:84%
And the biggest
complaint they have

00:29:14.470 --> 00:29:16.505 align:middle line:90%
is unresolved communication.

00:29:16.505 --> 00:29:17.380 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: It's true.

00:29:17.380 --> 00:29:19.421 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I wish I would've
said that to my mother.

00:29:19.421 --> 00:29:23.450 align:middle line:84%
I wish I'd not held onto
that with my brother.

00:29:23.450 --> 00:29:26.820 align:middle line:84%
And that they wanted
to go back and say it.

00:29:26.820 --> 00:29:27.520 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Yes.

00:29:27.520 --> 00:29:30.870 align:middle line:84%
And the amazing thing that
people don't understand

00:29:30.870 --> 00:29:34.510 align:middle line:90%
is, everything's renegotiable.

00:29:34.510 --> 00:29:35.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You can do that.

00:29:35.510 --> 00:29:36.800 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: You can do that.

00:29:36.800 --> 00:29:39.390 align:middle line:84%
It's that people don't
know how to find the words.

00:29:39.390 --> 00:29:40.980 align:middle line:84%
Their body starts
speaking and they

00:29:40.980 --> 00:29:43.105 align:middle line:84%
start getting so uncomfortable
that they don't even

00:29:43.105 --> 00:29:45.179 align:middle line:90%
think it's possible to do it.

00:29:45.179 --> 00:29:46.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
want to teach them.

00:29:46.720 --> 00:29:48.754 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Take marriage,
long term marriage.

00:29:48.754 --> 00:29:50.295 align:middle line:84%
And you're in a
marriage for so long,

00:29:50.295 --> 00:29:52.141 align:middle line:84%
and habits and patterns
take over sometimes.

00:29:52.141 --> 00:29:53.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: That's right.

00:29:53.140 --> 00:29:55.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And to even
say, look, I really

00:29:55.420 --> 00:29:57.085 align:middle line:84%
want to be this
way with you again.

00:29:57.085 --> 00:29:57.960 align:middle line:90%
Can we do this again?

00:29:57.960 --> 00:30:00.230 align:middle line:84%
There's not even-- it's so
tense-- oh god, how could I

00:30:00.230 --> 00:30:01.274 align:middle line:90%
possibly say that?

00:30:01.274 --> 00:30:01.940 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Yeah.

00:30:01.940 --> 00:30:03.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you're saying
override the wave.

00:30:03.880 --> 00:30:06.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: Well, it
repairs new tools.

00:30:06.290 --> 00:30:08.530 align:middle line:84%
One thing I don't want to
tell people or give them

00:30:08.530 --> 00:30:10.320 align:middle line:84%
the idea is like, oh,
all you have to do

00:30:10.320 --> 00:30:12.820 align:middle line:84%
is push through that discomfort
and you're going to be fine.

00:30:12.820 --> 00:30:14.720 align:middle line:84%
Because then what they're going
to do is have verbal vomit.

00:30:14.720 --> 00:30:15.370 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Oh, OK.

00:30:15.370 --> 00:30:15.930 align:middle line:10%
>>SANGWAN: You know,
they're just going to go--

00:30:15.930 --> 00:30:16.590 align:middle line:10%
[FAKE VOMITS]

00:30:16.590 --> 00:30:17.700 align:middle line:10%
--I need to tell
you all this stuff.

00:30:17.700 --> 00:30:18.810 align:middle line:10%
There's actually tools.

00:30:18.810 --> 00:30:20.643 align:middle line:10%
There's actually-- like,
when I was speaking

00:30:20.643 --> 00:30:22.680 align:middle line:10%
to you about the
example of the boss,

00:30:22.680 --> 00:30:25.225 align:middle line:10%
the first tool there was
you listening to your body

00:30:25.225 --> 00:30:26.940 align:middle line:10%
and connecting,
mapping out your body.

00:30:26.940 --> 00:30:27.885 align:middle line:10%
So doing a body map.

00:30:27.885 --> 00:30:29.010 align:middle line:10%
Figuring out what it means.

00:30:29.010 --> 00:30:31.520 align:middle line:10%
The second one was when I
came in and spoke to you,

00:30:31.520 --> 00:30:34.150 align:middle line:10%
I used I in my pronouns.

00:30:34.150 --> 00:30:34.937 align:middle line:90%
Not you.

00:30:34.937 --> 00:30:35.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great.

00:30:35.520 --> 00:30:37.910 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: So get out
of blaming, right?

00:30:37.910 --> 00:30:39.830 align:middle line:84%
Also, another tool
that we did there was I

00:30:39.830 --> 00:30:41.550 align:middle line:84%
set up the conversation
for success.

00:30:41.550 --> 00:30:44.080 align:middle line:84%
I told you the topic I
wanted to talk about,

00:30:44.080 --> 00:30:46.170 align:middle line:84%
I told you how
long it would take,

00:30:46.170 --> 00:30:48.230 align:middle line:84%
and I asked when was
a good time for you.

00:30:48.230 --> 00:30:50.170 align:middle line:84%
Those are all tools
that if people

00:30:50.170 --> 00:30:52.800 align:middle line:84%
aren't aware of how
to do these things,

00:30:52.800 --> 00:30:54.580 align:middle line:90%
they wonder why it's a disaster.

00:30:54.580 --> 00:30:55.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:30:55.480 --> 00:30:57.877 align:middle line:84%
So what are the most common
mistakes people make?

00:30:57.877 --> 00:30:59.710 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: In trying
to have a conversation?

00:30:59.710 --> 00:31:00.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:31:00.450 --> 00:31:01.527 align:middle line:90%
In speaking their truth.

00:31:01.527 --> 00:31:03.360 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: Is that they
think their truth is

00:31:03.360 --> 00:31:05.390 align:middle line:90%
about blaming somebody else.

00:31:05.390 --> 00:31:06.612 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: They did this to me.

00:31:06.612 --> 00:31:08.195 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: You did
this, you did that.

00:31:08.195 --> 00:31:08.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:31:08.450 --> 00:31:09.158 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Right?

00:31:09.158 --> 00:31:11.860 align:middle line:84%
And really, what I
want to say is, the way

00:31:11.860 --> 00:31:15.330 align:middle line:84%
that I-- so this is
what I heard or saw.

00:31:15.330 --> 00:31:17.464 align:middle line:84%
This is the story
I made up about it.

00:31:17.464 --> 00:31:19.130 align:middle line:84%
Because you don't
know if it's true yet.

00:31:19.130 --> 00:31:19.838 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, true.

00:31:19.838 --> 00:31:21.620 align:middle line:84%
You can make a big
story up about it.

00:31:21.620 --> 00:31:24.040 align:middle line:84%
This, then this, then they
said that and they felt that.

00:31:24.040 --> 00:31:24.660 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: You know what?

00:31:24.660 --> 00:31:25.970 align:middle line:90%
And I saw her talking to him.

00:31:25.970 --> 00:31:26.860 align:middle line:84%
And you know what
they were about?

00:31:26.860 --> 00:31:28.370 align:middle line:90%
They were talking about us.

00:31:28.370 --> 00:31:28.950 align:middle line:90%
I knew it.

00:31:28.950 --> 00:31:30.221 align:middle line:90%
I knew-- did you see them?

00:31:30.221 --> 00:31:31.720 align:middle line:84%
And meanwhile, I've
never asked them

00:31:31.720 --> 00:31:32.450 align:middle line:90%
what they were talking about.

00:31:32.450 --> 00:31:33.220 align:middle line:84%
They might have
just been talking

00:31:33.220 --> 00:31:34.670 align:middle line:84%
about the latest show
they're going to.

00:31:34.670 --> 00:31:35.211 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:31:35.211 --> 00:31:38.050 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: But I am so sure
that my insecurities and what

00:31:38.050 --> 00:31:39.922 align:middle line:90%
stories I'm making up are true.

00:31:39.922 --> 00:31:42.130 align:middle line:84%
So that's the second big
mistake I think people make,

00:31:42.130 --> 00:31:44.360 align:middle line:90%
which is they don't get curious.

00:31:44.360 --> 00:31:50.720 align:middle line:84%
So one of the things I say
is get curious, not furious.

00:31:50.720 --> 00:31:51.320 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:31:51.320 --> 00:31:53.820 align:middle line:84%
Because first figure out
if whatever you're thinking

00:31:53.820 --> 00:31:54.596 align:middle line:90%
is true.

00:31:54.596 --> 00:31:55.970 align:middle line:84%
And then I think
really what they

00:31:55.970 --> 00:31:57.761 align:middle line:84%
need to do is be clear
about what they want

00:31:57.761 --> 00:32:00.010 align:middle line:84%
and what they value in order
to make clear decisions,

00:32:00.010 --> 00:32:01.718 align:middle line:84%
and know what you want
to say to someone.

00:32:01.718 --> 00:32:03.892 align:middle line:84%
What do you want out
of this conversation?

00:32:03.892 --> 00:32:04.975 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What do you value?

00:32:04.975 --> 00:32:06.091 align:middle line:90%
That's a good point.

00:32:06.091 --> 00:32:06.840 align:middle line:90%
What do you value?

00:32:06.840 --> 00:32:09.850 align:middle line:84%
So think about
that ahead of time.

00:32:09.850 --> 00:32:11.420 align:middle line:84%
You want to improve
the relationship.

00:32:11.420 --> 00:32:13.310 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to let go
of the relationship?

00:32:13.310 --> 00:32:14.310 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: That's right.

00:32:14.310 --> 00:32:15.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you think
about that ahead of time.

00:32:15.890 --> 00:32:18.056 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: Yeah, you want
to know, what do you want?

00:32:18.056 --> 00:32:20.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's more that we
can grab onto tools when

00:32:20.400 --> 00:32:22.435 align:middle line:90%
we're in that moment of, oh god.

00:32:22.435 --> 00:32:25.466 align:middle line:84%
You can just file it through
in your mind and go, OK.

00:32:25.466 --> 00:32:26.590 align:middle line:90%
This, this, this, and this.

00:32:26.590 --> 00:32:29.090 align:middle line:84%
Not that it disconnects you
from your emotion, but sometimes

00:32:29.090 --> 00:32:30.814 align:middle line:84%
it just is a great
starting point.

00:32:30.814 --> 00:32:31.480 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Yeah.

00:32:31.480 --> 00:32:33.760 align:middle line:84%
And it actually helps you
process your emotions.

00:32:33.760 --> 00:32:37.380 align:middle line:84%
Because if I say yes to you
to doing something and then

00:32:37.380 --> 00:32:39.600 align:middle line:90%
I notice that I'm afraid, right?

00:32:39.600 --> 00:32:44.041 align:middle line:84%
I told you when I said I'd do
the book deal I was petrified,

00:32:44.041 --> 00:32:44.540 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:32:44.540 --> 00:32:45.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:32:45.180 --> 00:32:45.680 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:32:45.680 --> 00:32:48.460 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: And in that fear now,
now that helps me get curious.

00:32:48.460 --> 00:32:51.372 align:middle line:84%
Am I fearful because
I don't think

00:32:51.372 --> 00:32:52.580 align:middle line:90%
it's going to be a good book?

00:32:52.580 --> 00:32:55.022 align:middle line:84%
Am I fearful because I
