What changes?

00:42:55.690 --> 00:42:58.140 align:middle line:90%
How do you know it's coming?

00:42:58.140 --> 00:43:00.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: He will
just blurt it out.

00:43:00.080 --> 00:43:03.480 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: So he'll
maybe speak quick, loud?

00:43:03.480 --> 00:43:05.792 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It will be awkward, too.

00:43:05.792 --> 00:43:06.750 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Like abrupt?

00:43:06.750 --> 00:43:07.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, abrupt.

00:43:07.100 --> 00:43:07.900 align:middle line:90%
That's a good word for it.

00:43:07.900 --> 00:43:08.210 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:43:08.210 --> 00:43:09.750 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: So he'll speak
and it'll be like this, ah!

00:43:09.750 --> 00:43:10.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:43:10.010 --> 00:43:10.980 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: He'll
say whatever it is.

00:43:10.980 --> 00:43:11.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:43:11.230 --> 00:43:11.850 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: OK.

00:43:11.850 --> 00:43:14.130 align:middle line:84%
So in that moment
what happens is

00:43:14.130 --> 00:43:16.690 align:middle line:84%
that you become that
eight-year-old little girl.

00:43:16.690 --> 00:43:19.240 align:middle line:84%
It's called in your
amygdala in your brain

00:43:19.240 --> 00:43:21.560 align:middle line:84%
where it stores the
memories of things

00:43:21.560 --> 00:43:24.740 align:middle line:84%
that felt traumatic or unsafe
for you when you were little.

00:43:24.740 --> 00:43:27.360 align:middle line:84%
So all of the sudden,
you become as effective

00:43:27.360 --> 00:43:30.090 align:middle line:84%
as that eight-year-old
little girl.

00:43:30.090 --> 00:43:31.724 align:middle line:84%
And so what you
want to do is-- I

00:43:31.724 --> 00:43:33.140 align:middle line:84%
don't know if your
husband's going

00:43:33.140 --> 00:43:35.820 align:middle line:84%
to appreciate me saying
all this, but here we go.

00:43:35.820 --> 00:43:38.810 align:middle line:84%
Next time he blurts
something out,

00:43:38.810 --> 00:43:41.990 align:middle line:84%
I want you to take
a really deep breath

00:43:41.990 --> 00:43:43.704 align:middle line:84%
and notice the physical
sensations that

00:43:43.704 --> 00:43:44.620 align:middle line:90%
are happening for you.

00:43:44.620 --> 00:43:45.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:43:45.120 --> 00:43:46.250 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: OK?

00:43:46.250 --> 00:43:49.680 align:middle line:84%
When he's having that
moment of just saying it,

00:43:49.680 --> 00:43:51.780 align:middle line:84%
you can imagine that
he's pretty uncomfortable

00:43:51.780 --> 00:43:53.711 align:middle line:90%
and stressed too, OK?

00:43:53.711 --> 00:43:54.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:43:54.210 --> 00:43:57.880 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: And usually when
people are blurting something

00:43:57.880 --> 00:43:59.690 align:middle line:84%
out or they're just
saying it like that,

00:43:59.690 --> 00:44:02.970 align:middle line:84%
it's because they're
dispelling their discomfort.

00:44:02.970 --> 00:44:06.540 align:middle line:84%
And so if he was a little
kid, what would you

00:44:06.540 --> 00:44:08.580 align:middle line:84%
do to that little--
What would you say?

00:44:08.580 --> 00:44:11.810 align:middle line:84%
What would you do with that
little kid who had that moment?

00:44:11.810 --> 00:44:14.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I realize that you might
feel uncomfortable right now.

00:44:14.740 --> 00:44:16.870 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: Yeah, you might even
pick him up and give him a hug,

00:44:16.870 --> 00:44:17.369 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:44:17.369 --> 00:44:18.380 align:middle line:90%
If he was little.

00:44:18.380 --> 00:44:18.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:44:18.600 --> 00:44:20.070 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: He just
happens to be your size

00:44:20.070 --> 00:44:22.920 align:middle line:84%
and connected to your heart and
love and all that stuff, right?

00:44:22.920 --> 00:44:23.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:44:23.500 --> 00:44:25.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: So what I
want you to do next time

00:44:25.610 --> 00:44:31.110 align:middle line:84%
is imagine him little and
he's having this experience.

00:44:31.110 --> 00:44:33.230 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to
see yourself as big.

00:44:33.230 --> 00:44:34.550 align:middle line:90%
You're not eight anymore.

00:44:34.550 --> 00:44:36.092 align:middle line:90%
You're grown up.

00:44:36.092 --> 00:44:38.300 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to imagine
him, and what would you do?

00:44:38.300 --> 00:44:40.050 align:middle line:90%
You'd give compassion.

00:44:40.050 --> 00:44:43.350 align:middle line:84%
You'd get curious about
that child, right?

00:44:43.350 --> 00:44:45.530 align:middle line:84%
And what's happening,
and what's hurting him?

00:44:45.530 --> 00:44:48.679 align:middle line:84%
So I want you to just take that
moment, take a deep breath.

00:44:48.679 --> 00:44:50.720 align:middle line:84%
Imagine that he's trying
to communicate something

00:44:50.720 --> 00:44:54.120 align:middle line:84%
to you that he thinks
you might not be getting.

00:44:54.120 --> 00:44:56.060 align:middle line:84%
And get curious
and compassionate.

00:44:56.060 --> 00:44:59.080 align:middle line:84%
I want you to ask yourself, what
would curiosity and compassion

00:44:59.080 --> 00:45:01.030 align:middle line:90%
do now?

00:45:01.030 --> 00:45:02.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Ask myself
in that moment?

00:45:02.750 --> 00:45:07.835 align:middle line:84%
And then just do that, just take
a minute or hug him or agree?

00:45:07.835 --> 00:45:10.460 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: You might not want to
hug him in that moment, right?

00:45:10.460 --> 00:45:11.880 align:middle line:84%
Because that might be
too big of a stretch.

00:45:11.880 --> 00:45:12.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:45:12.400 --> 00:45:14.775 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: But what you might
want to say-- otherwise you

00:45:14.775 --> 00:45:16.650 align:middle line:84%
make a pact with him
outside of that time.

00:45:16.650 --> 00:45:18.049 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah, good idea.

00:45:18.049 --> 00:45:19.590 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: And it
can be like, honey,

00:45:19.590 --> 00:45:22.420 align:middle line:84%
when we do this what it
means is we just stop.

00:45:22.420 --> 00:45:23.879 align:middle line:84%
And you figure out
how you connect.

00:45:23.879 --> 00:45:26.336 align:middle line:84%
If it is through a hug and you
feel like you could do that,

00:45:26.336 --> 00:45:27.000 align:middle line:90%
try it.

00:45:27.000 --> 00:45:29.079 align:middle line:84%
You can always renegotiate
it if it doesn't work.

00:45:29.079 --> 00:45:30.620 align:middle line:84%
If what you do is
go like this and it

00:45:30.620 --> 00:45:33.770 align:middle line:84%
means we both get to go
for a walk in 15 minutes

00:45:33.770 --> 00:45:36.090 align:middle line:84%
and meet back here and have
tea and do our own thing

00:45:36.090 --> 00:45:38.160 align:middle line:90%
and have that talk, we do that.

00:45:38.160 --> 00:45:41.550 align:middle line:84%
But two people need to
negotiate between each other

00:45:41.550 --> 00:45:42.980 align:middle line:90%
how to make that different.

00:45:42.980 --> 00:45:44.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And set it
up ahead of time.

00:45:44.480 --> 00:45:46.500 align:middle line:84%
We have a phrase
called white flag.

00:45:46.500 --> 00:45:49.595 align:middle line:84%
Like, if there's a moment
where we're both off the rails,

00:45:49.595 --> 00:45:50.470 align:middle line:90%
we say, "White flag."

00:45:50.470 --> 00:45:51.347 align:middle line:90%
Walk away.

00:45:51.347 --> 00:45:53.430 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll figure it
out later, but that's it.

00:45:53.430 --> 00:45:55.763 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: But what are you
going to do in those moments

00:45:55.763 --> 00:45:59.720 align:middle line:84%
when you do get to figure it out
later that changes the outcome?

00:45:59.720 --> 00:46:02.740 align:middle line:84%
And for you it's going to
be curiosity and compassion.

00:46:02.740 --> 00:46:05.437 align:middle line:84%
You think it's for him,
but it's actually not.

00:46:05.437 --> 00:46:06.270 align:middle line:90%
You know what it is?

00:46:06.270 --> 00:46:08.320 align:middle line:84%
It's for that
eight-year-old little girl

00:46:08.320 --> 00:46:11.680 align:middle line:84%
that was scared, that felt
like her voice didn't matter.

00:46:11.680 --> 00:46:14.080 align:middle line:84%
It's for her that you're
becoming compassionate.

00:46:14.080 --> 00:46:16.780 align:middle line:84%
And as you start doing
that, your husband actually

00:46:16.780 --> 00:46:19.700 align:middle line:84%
ends up being your greatest
teacher because he allows

00:46:19.700 --> 00:46:23.030 align:middle line:84%
you to access that little
girl and help heal her.

00:46:23.030 --> 00:46:25.860 align:middle line:84%
So he actually becomes
a big gift in your life.

00:46:25.860 --> 00:46:26.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:46:26.380 --> 00:46:27.910 align:middle line:90%
Talking about a gift.

00:46:27.910 --> 00:46:28.880 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Yeah.

00:46:28.880 --> 00:46:30.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You are a
gift to many people.

00:46:30.780 --> 00:46:31.692 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Thank you.

00:46:31.692 --> 00:46:33.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Let's talk
about headaches.

