00:48:20.510 --> 00:48:22.260 align:middle line:84%
You get to get off the
hook with yourself.

00:48:22.260 --> 00:48:23.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:48:23.830 --> 00:48:27.040 align:middle line:84%
And along those
lines, breathing.

00:48:27.040 --> 00:48:28.010 align:middle line:90%
Asthma.

00:48:28.010 --> 00:48:28.780 align:middle line:90%
Asthma.

00:48:28.780 --> 00:48:31.340 align:middle line:84%
Where do you see--
you have a technique

00:48:31.340 --> 00:48:32.930 align:middle line:84%
that you teach
around breath, right?

00:48:32.930 --> 00:48:33.977 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Yeah, I do.

00:48:33.977 --> 00:48:35.560 align:middle line:84%
And it's really just
simple breathing.

00:48:35.560 --> 00:48:40.050 align:middle line:84%
First of all, stress exacerbates
or causes more than 95%

00:48:40.050 --> 00:48:40.680 align:middle line:90%
of illness.

00:48:40.680 --> 00:48:41.319 align:middle line:90%
We know that.

00:48:41.319 --> 00:48:42.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's been
very well proven.

00:48:42.860 --> 00:48:43.145 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Right.

00:48:43.145 --> 00:48:44.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I've heard higher.

00:48:44.370 --> 00:48:45.240 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Even higher, right?

00:48:45.240 --> 00:48:46.323 align:middle line:90%
Some people say it's 100%.

00:48:46.323 --> 00:48:48.520 align:middle line:90%
Everything is induced.

00:48:48.520 --> 00:48:51.780 align:middle line:84%
Stress also decreases our
immune function, right?

00:48:51.780 --> 00:48:56.730 align:middle line:84%
And so our immune function is
when we repair things, right?

00:48:56.730 --> 00:48:58.147 align:middle line:90%
It's our defense system.

00:48:58.147 --> 00:48:58.980 align:middle line:90%
It takes care of us.

00:48:58.980 --> 00:49:01.990 align:middle line:84%
And so asthma is a reactive
airway disease, right?

00:49:01.990 --> 00:49:05.240 align:middle line:84%
And so that's like the your
lungs and all the branches

00:49:05.240 --> 00:49:08.620 align:middle line:84%
of the air sacs in there,
they have muscles around them.

00:49:08.620 --> 00:49:11.330 align:middle line:84%
And it's like a
reaction that happens.

00:49:11.330 --> 00:49:12.920 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's from
an allergy outside,

00:49:12.920 --> 00:49:15.474 align:middle line:84%
whether it's from an
emotional response,

00:49:15.474 --> 00:49:16.890 align:middle line:84%
there's a reactivity
that happens.

00:49:16.890 --> 00:49:18.501 align:middle line:90%
And you cannot take in breath.

00:49:18.501 --> 00:49:19.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, interesting.

00:49:19.500 --> 00:49:23.010 align:middle line:84%
So it's a constriction of
little muscles in the lungs.

00:49:23.010 --> 00:49:26.100 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: And so the
interesting thing, yeah.

00:49:26.100 --> 00:49:26.840 align:middle line:90%
There is a link.

00:49:26.840 --> 00:49:28.580 align:middle line:90%
There's a link to cold weather.

00:49:28.580 --> 00:49:30.450 align:middle line:84%
There's a link to
all sorts of things.

00:49:30.450 --> 00:49:32.650 align:middle line:84%
I do believe there's
also an emotional link.

00:49:32.650 --> 00:49:35.300 align:middle line:84%
Of course that's my lens, so
I realize that I sometimes

00:49:35.300 --> 00:49:36.670 align:middle line:90%
see it through that lens.

00:49:36.670 --> 00:49:38.750 align:middle line:84%
And stress gets a
big bucket, right?

00:49:38.750 --> 00:49:41.560 align:middle line:84%
But it's around what actually
causes that at the bottom.

00:49:41.560 --> 00:49:43.460 align:middle line:84%
So you were asking
about breathing, right?

00:49:43.460 --> 00:49:45.640 align:middle line:90%
So really quick.

