00:49:57.000 --> 00:49:57.740 align:middle line:90%
[GASPS]

00:49:57.740 --> 00:49:58.471 align:middle line:90%
What if?

00:49:58.471 --> 00:49:58.970 align:middle line:90%
What if?

00:49:58.970 --> 00:50:00.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's how
they got there, yeah.

00:50:00.090 --> 00:50:01.500 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: OK, so they're
all sitting there.

00:50:01.500 --> 00:50:03.060 align:middle line:84%
So I would get
called downstairs.

00:50:03.060 --> 00:50:06.640 align:middle line:84%
And they would say, "Dr.
Sangwan, this person

00:50:06.640 --> 00:50:10.600 align:middle line:84%
is having a heart
rate of 110, and we

00:50:10.600 --> 00:50:12.680 align:middle line:84%
think that you
need to see them."

00:50:12.680 --> 00:50:14.860 align:middle line:84%
I'd come downstairs
and they would

00:50:14.860 --> 00:50:16.340 align:middle line:90%
be breathing just like this.

00:50:16.340 --> 00:50:18.310 align:middle line:90%
[SHARP GASPS]

00:50:18.310 --> 00:50:19.522 align:middle line:90%
No, doc, I'm breathing.

00:50:19.522 --> 00:50:21.480 align:middle line:84%
But what they were doing
was reverse breathing.

00:50:21.480 --> 00:50:24.151 align:middle line:84%
So what I'm going to show you
right now is to actually--

00:50:24.151 --> 00:50:25.650 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to
uncross our legs.

00:50:25.650 --> 00:50:25.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:50:25.940 --> 00:50:26.546 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: OK?

00:50:26.546 --> 00:50:27.670 align:middle line:90%
Put our feet on the ground.

00:50:27.670 --> 00:50:30.550 align:middle line:84%
And this helps with
any kind of anxiety.

00:50:30.550 --> 00:50:32.850 align:middle line:84%
And so what you want to do
is you have to-- anxiety

00:50:32.850 --> 00:50:34.630 align:middle line:84%
is a fear about
what might happen.

00:50:34.630 --> 00:50:36.772 align:middle line:84%
It's trying to
control the future.

00:50:36.772 --> 00:50:37.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, wow.

00:50:37.680 --> 00:50:38.510 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: OK?

00:50:38.510 --> 00:50:42.880 align:middle line:84%
So one of the antidotes to
that, and I speak about this,

00:50:42.880 --> 00:50:45.220 align:middle line:84%
is that you want to
get in the present.

00:50:45.220 --> 00:50:47.090 align:middle line:84%
You need to get someone
who's having a panic

00:50:47.090 --> 00:50:48.590 align:middle line:84%
attack in the present
moment, right?

00:50:48.590 --> 00:50:51.006 align:middle line:84%
So the first thing you do is
get their feet on the ground,

00:50:51.006 --> 00:50:52.900 align:middle line:90%
get them to take a deep breath.

00:50:52.900 --> 00:50:54.840 align:middle line:84%
And when they do
I'm going ask you

00:50:54.840 --> 00:50:59.250 align:middle line:84%
to feel your ribcage
expanding and contracting.

00:50:59.250 --> 00:51:01.695 align:middle line:84%
Bring awareness to your ribcage
expanding and contracting.

00:51:01.695 --> 00:51:03.654 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you have to
breathe deep to do that.

00:51:03.654 --> 00:51:04.361 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Right?

00:51:04.361 --> 00:51:06.560 align:middle line:84%
And we're taught as women,
hold your stomach in.

00:51:06.560 --> 00:51:07.847 align:middle line:90%
Suck it in, right?

00:51:07.847 --> 00:51:08.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:51:08.430 --> 00:51:09.013 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: OK.

00:51:09.013 --> 00:51:11.770 align:middle line:84%
Now you're going to put your
hand on your abdomen, OK?

00:51:11.770 --> 00:51:13.728 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to take
a nice deep breath in.

00:51:13.728 --> 00:51:17.210 align:middle line:84%
And as you do, I want
your hand to move outward.

00:51:17.210 --> 00:51:19.220 align:middle line:84%
And as you breathe out,
I want your belly button

00:51:19.220 --> 00:51:20.790 align:middle line:90%
to move back towards your spine.

00:51:20.790 --> 00:51:22.045 align:middle line:90%
[BREATHING]

00:51:22.045 --> 00:51:23.643 align:middle line:84%
And then I want you
to take two more.

00:51:23.643 --> 00:51:25.740 align:middle line:90%
[BREATHING]

00:51:25.740 --> 00:51:26.780 align:middle line:90%
And breathe out.

00:51:26.780 --> 00:51:30.100 align:middle line:84%
Belly button back
toward your spine.

00:51:30.100 --> 00:51:30.765 align:middle line:90%
And one more.

00:51:30.765 --> 00:51:34.542 align:middle line:90%
[BREATHING]

00:51:34.542 --> 00:51:37.474 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That actually allows me
to really think clearly, too.

00:51:37.474 --> 00:51:40.015 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: So what it does is
it brings oxygen to your brain.

00:51:40.015 --> 00:51:41.570 align:middle line:84%
When people are in
fear or panicked

00:51:41.570 --> 00:51:43.320 align:middle line:84%
or having that discomfort
you were talking

00:51:43.320 --> 00:51:46.009 align:middle line:84%
about with your husband,
they stop breathing.

00:51:46.009 --> 00:51:48.050 align:middle line:84%
Or they do that reverse
breathing where they're--

00:51:48.050 --> 00:51:49.750 align:middle line:90%
[SHARP GASPS]

00:51:49.750 --> 00:51:50.870 align:middle line:90%
--they're doing this, OK?

00:51:50.870 --> 00:51:52.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or just
chest up breathing.

00:51:52.200 --> 00:51:52.780 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Chest up, right?

00:51:52.780 --> 00:51:55.460 align:middle line:10%
So where does the best oxygen
exchange occur in your body?

00:51:55.460 --> 00:51:56.960 align:middle line:10%
Your lungs go all
the way down here.

00:51:56.960 --> 00:51:59.990 align:middle line:10%
And it occurs at the
bases of your lungs.

00:51:59.990 --> 00:52:01.740 align:middle line:84%
So we don't usually--
we're running around

00:52:01.740 --> 00:52:02.640 align:middle line:90%
in our busy world.

00:52:02.640 --> 00:52:04.852 align:middle line:84%
We only use this-- hey, do
you want to go to lunch?

00:52:04.852 --> 00:52:06.060 align:middle line:90%
Hey, can you get that for me?

00:52:06.060 --> 00:52:08.659 align:middle line:10%
We're only using this
much of our lungs.

00:52:08.659 --> 00:52:10.700 align:middle line:10%
So what happens here is,
you have this diaphragm.

00:52:10.700 --> 00:52:12.500 align:middle line:10%
It's a thin muscle.

00:52:12.500 --> 00:52:13.970 align:middle line:90%
And it looks like an umbrella.

00:52:13.970 --> 00:52:17.280 align:middle line:84%
And it's below your lungs
and above your stomach, OK?

00:52:17.280 --> 00:52:21.020 align:middle line:84%
When you take a
deep breath in, that

00:52:21.020 --> 00:52:24.370 align:middle line:84%
must flatten in order
to keep the air going.

00:52:24.370 --> 00:52:26.330 align:middle line:90%
That triggers your vagus nerve.

00:52:26.330 --> 00:52:30.660 align:middle line:84%
And that slows down your
heart rate, calms you.

00:52:30.660 --> 00:52:33.204 align:middle line:84%
You start to get air,
oxygen to your brain.

00:52:33.204 --> 00:52:35.120 align:middle line:84%
All of the sudden now
you're thinking clearly,

00:52:35.120 --> 00:52:37.680 align:middle line:84%
creative options, instead of
do I have to get out of here

00:52:37.680 --> 00:52:38.340 align:middle line:90%
or shut down?

00:52:38.340 --> 00:52:39.965 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I love the
medical definitions.

00:52:39.965 --> 00:52:40.844 align:middle line:90%
You're right.

00:52:40.844 --> 00:52:42.885 align:middle line:84%
The vagus nerve that runs
through the whole body.

00:52:42.885 --> 00:52:45.129 align:middle line:84%
And it controls the
central nervous system?

00:52:45.129 --> 00:52:47.420 align:middle line:84%
>>SANGWAN: It hits your
parasympathetic nervous system,

00:52:47.420 --> 00:52:49.100 align:middle line:90%
which is your relaxation system.

00:52:49.100 --> 00:52:51.180 align:middle line:84%
And it runs through
the diaphragm.

00:52:51.180 --> 00:52:53.190 align:middle line:84%
So when you start
stimulating the diaphragm,

00:52:53.190 --> 00:52:54.690 align:middle line:90%
you're stimulating your vagus.

00:52:54.690 --> 00:52:57.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow, that's fabulous.

00:52:57.740 --> 00:52:59.660 align:middle line:84%
That's a great way of
visualizing it as well.

00:52:59.660 --> 00:53:00.352 align:middle line:90%
>>SANGWAN: Yeah.

00:53:00.352 --> 00:53:03.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it helps you make
decisions, become clearer.

00:53:03.280 --> 00:53:04.810 align:middle line:84%
I actually was
talking about that.

00:53:04.810 --> 00:53:06.640 align:middle line:84%
I got really clear
in that moment.

