00:53:15.750 --> 00:53:19.270 align:middle line:84%
-Hi, this is Dr. Neha,
and welcome to my vlog.

00:53:19.270 --> 00:53:23.030 align:middle line:84%
Today's topic is on
decision fatigue.

00:53:23.030 --> 00:53:25.060 align:middle line:84%
Several of my clients
over the past few weeks

00:53:25.060 --> 00:53:27.530 align:middle line:84%
have been asking
me, "Dr. Neha, how

00:53:27.530 --> 00:53:30.262 align:middle line:84%
do I know, if I've
made a decision,

00:53:30.262 --> 00:53:31.970 align:middle line:84%
whether it was the
right decision or not?

00:53:31.970 --> 00:53:34.090 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's about
going to the movies

00:53:34.090 --> 00:53:37.670 align:middle line:84%
with a friend when I was
really tired after work,

00:53:37.670 --> 00:53:40.570 align:middle line:90%
or am I in the right job?

00:53:40.570 --> 00:53:42.490 align:middle line:90%
How do you actually know?"

00:53:42.490 --> 00:53:45.950 align:middle line:84%
So it brought me
back to my life,

00:53:45.950 --> 00:53:48.310 align:middle line:84%
because they often
ask me, "Dr. Neha,

00:53:48.310 --> 00:53:51.200 align:middle line:84%
how did you become
a doctor of science,

00:53:51.200 --> 00:53:53.810 align:middle line:84%
initially a doctor of
medicine, and then transition

00:53:53.810 --> 00:53:56.530 align:middle line:84%
into being a doctor
of communication?"

00:53:56.530 --> 00:54:00.950 align:middle line:84%
So first of all, I want to
say it wasn't that easy.

00:54:00.950 --> 00:54:03.980 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't like I woke up
one day and I just knew.

00:54:03.980 --> 00:54:06.100 align:middle line:84%
It was a series of
experiences where

00:54:06.100 --> 00:54:08.340 align:middle line:84%
I had to listen to my
body and pay attention.

00:54:08.340 --> 00:54:10.090 align:middle line:84%
What I'm going to do
today is just distill

00:54:10.090 --> 00:54:13.540 align:middle line:84%
that down to a few
easy steps for you.

00:54:13.540 --> 00:54:18.230 align:middle line:84%
So I used to work in a
more corporate environment

00:54:18.230 --> 00:54:20.120 align:middle line:90%
and also in a hospital.

00:54:20.120 --> 00:54:24.240 align:middle line:84%
And one thing I'd notice is
I did well for a few months,

00:54:24.240 --> 00:54:27.080 align:middle line:84%
and then my energy would
continue to go down and down.

00:54:27.080 --> 00:54:28.280 align:middle line:90%
I would feel drained.

00:54:28.280 --> 00:54:32.070 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately I would feel
like I was almost a burnout.

00:54:32.070 --> 00:54:33.980 align:middle line:84%
And then I would rest
or take a vacation,

00:54:33.980 --> 00:54:36.400 align:middle line:84%
and then I would be
back to normal again.

00:54:36.400 --> 00:54:38.980 align:middle line:84%
And this went on and
on until I finally

00:54:38.980 --> 00:54:41.920 align:middle line:84%
started getting so tired
that I wasn't recovering.

00:54:41.920 --> 00:54:44.390 align:middle line:84%
And so what happened
for me was I noticed

00:54:44.390 --> 00:54:48.790 align:middle line:84%
when I was with my clients or my
patients, I really got charged.

00:54:48.790 --> 00:54:51.670 align:middle line:84%
I had a lot of energy when
we had a really good exchange

00:54:51.670 --> 00:54:54.410 align:middle line:84%
about their life and what
their illness meant to them

00:54:54.410 --> 00:54:57.640 align:middle line:84%
in their life, and how it would
help them change their life.

00:54:57.640 --> 00:55:00.640 align:middle line:84%
And I had a lot of
energy in me when

00:55:00.640 --> 00:55:02.220 align:middle line:84%
I'd go to communication
workshops.

00:55:02.220 --> 00:55:05.980 align:middle line:84%
Or when I'd be talking to
a girlfriend on a Saturday,

00:55:05.980 --> 00:55:09.100 align:middle line:84%
you know, about how
to change my life

00:55:09.100 --> 00:55:13.744 align:middle line:84%
and how to feel inspired
about what's coming up.

00:55:13.744 --> 00:55:15.410 align:middle line:84%
We would have these
great conversations.

00:55:15.410 --> 00:55:18.410 align:middle line:84%
All of these items were
around communication.

00:55:18.410 --> 00:55:20.780 align:middle line:90%
So I started to pay attention.

00:55:20.780 --> 00:55:23.840 align:middle line:84%
I also learned that I
enjoyed working with people.

00:55:23.840 --> 00:55:25.120 align:middle line:90%
I'm a doctor.

00:55:25.120 --> 00:55:27.380 align:middle line:84%
Working with patients
was fantastic.

00:55:27.380 --> 00:55:29.820 align:middle line:90%
So I knew that I valued people.

00:55:29.820 --> 00:55:33.770 align:middle line:84%
And I started to notice
when I felt more energy.

00:55:33.770 --> 00:55:36.575 align:middle line:84%
So I felt more energy when I
was around people and we we

00:55:36.575 --> 00:55:38.700 align:middle line:84%
were talking about
communication.

00:55:38.700 --> 00:55:46.160 align:middle line:84%
So what I call-- the problem
with decision fatigue is, A,

00:55:46.160 --> 00:55:48.956 align:middle line:84%
people are not paying attention
to their body's signals

00:55:48.956 --> 00:55:49.830 align:middle line:90%
that they're getting.

00:55:49.830 --> 00:55:51.900 align:middle line:84%
I used to get
throat constriction.

00:55:51.900 --> 00:55:53.410 align:middle line:84%
I used to have my
stomach turning.

00:55:53.410 --> 00:55:55.430 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't paying
attention to any of that.

00:55:55.430 --> 00:55:57.020 align:middle line:84%
I was just powering
through my day.

00:55:57.020 --> 00:56:02.380 align:middle line:84%
So my first question is, do
you know when you have energy?

00:56:02.380 --> 00:56:05.220 align:middle line:84%
When you feel you've
increased your energy,

00:56:05.220 --> 00:56:06.535 align:middle line:90%
how does your body tell you?

00:56:06.535 --> 00:56:09.540 align:middle line:84%
And when you feel
drained of energy, how

00:56:09.540 --> 00:56:11.610 align:middle line:90%
does your body tell you?

00:56:11.610 --> 00:56:13.475 align:middle line:84%
So you have to know
those two things first.

00:56:13.475 --> 00:56:15.100 align:middle line:84%
And then I'm going
to teach you the two

00:56:15.100 --> 00:56:18.240 align:middle line:90%
steps to making good decisions.

00:56:18.240 --> 00:56:20.700 align:middle line:84%
So I call it the
decision filter test.

00:56:20.700 --> 00:56:23.610 align:middle line:84%
Step one is knowing
what you value.

00:56:23.610 --> 00:56:24.490 align:middle line:90%
I value people.

00:56:24.490 --> 00:56:27.950 align:middle line:84%
I value healing, health
and communication, love

00:56:27.950 --> 00:56:29.250 align:middle line:90%
and connection.

00:56:29.250 --> 00:56:32.220 align:middle line:84%
Those are all really,
really important to me.

00:56:32.220 --> 00:56:36.410 align:middle line:84%
So if I know what I value,
then all I need to know

00:56:36.410 --> 00:56:40.397 align:middle line:84%
is step two, which is what gives
me energy and what drains me

00:56:40.397 --> 00:56:42.160 align:middle line:90%
of energy?

00:56:42.160 --> 00:56:44.540 align:middle line:84%
So an exercise where
you can do this

00:56:44.540 --> 00:56:49.320 align:middle line:84%
is to actually spend the next
seven days, the next week,

00:56:49.320 --> 00:56:50.840 align:middle line:90%
just paying attention.

00:56:50.840 --> 00:56:54.990 align:middle line:84%
What interactions, situations,
conversations give you energy,

00:56:54.990 --> 00:56:57.110 align:middle line:90%
and which ones drain you?

00:56:57.110 --> 00:56:59.750 align:middle line:90%
And then the part on values.

00:56:59.750 --> 00:57:02.215 align:middle line:84%
What you want to do is,
if you don't know right

00:57:02.215 --> 00:57:05.250 align:middle line:84%
off the top of your head-- most
people don't know what they

00:57:05.250 --> 00:57:07.630 align:middle line:84%
value, what you do
is think of someone

00:57:07.630 --> 00:57:11.460 align:middle line:84%
you really admire,
someone in the world

00:57:11.460 --> 00:57:15.120 align:middle line:90%
who seems to have what you want.

00:57:15.120 --> 00:57:20.840 align:middle line:84%
And pay attention to what
it is you value about them.

00:57:20.840 --> 00:57:23.184 align:middle line:84%
Write those three
to five things down.

00:57:23.184 --> 00:57:24.600 align:middle line:84%
And then I want
you to know, those

00:57:24.600 --> 00:57:29.260 align:middle line:84%
are actually some of
what you value most.

00:57:29.260 --> 00:57:31.510 align:middle line:84%
So you're just going to put
those two things together.

00:57:31.510 --> 00:57:32.510 align:middle line:84%
And when you have
a decision that

00:57:32.510 --> 00:57:34.310 align:middle line:84%
comes your way, ask
yourself, does it

00:57:34.310 --> 00:57:37.100 align:middle line:90%
pass has my values filter test?

00:57:37.100 --> 00:57:38.860 align:middle line:84%
I think of it like
a little filter.

00:57:38.860 --> 00:57:41.420 align:middle line:84%
Does it pass my
values filter test?

00:57:41.420 --> 00:57:43.090 align:middle line:84%
And if it does,
the second question

00:57:43.090 --> 00:57:45.240 align:middle line:90%
is do I want to do this?

00:57:45.240 --> 00:57:48.580 align:middle line:84%
And you know that if
it gives you energy.

00:57:48.580 --> 00:57:51.100 align:middle line:84%
So I hope that the
values filter test

00:57:51.100 --> 00:57:53.252 align:middle line:84%
will help making
decisions for you easier.

